column5: I landed 3 pike today between 10:30 and 11:00.  2 of them were between 26 and 29 inches and fat.  Lost 2 more during that time and missed a half dozen others that followed and pecked.  Small spinners, especially silver (on a sunny day) were most effective.  Water temperature and cabbage seem ideal.  Lots of boat traffic in the afternoon didn't help.  Surface weeds are starting to fill in and will be a problem for casting and trolling with the sunny and hot forecast for the coming week.
Right on buddy, the two Pike I caught here in Oshawa were shorter and fat...but with the warm start...there gone from the bays
Near Hanlans Point? On the old docks?
Good job yakpiker. A small gaggle of yakfishermen from Yakfisher.net were heading to the islands from Cherry Beach today. Did you hook up with them?
Yep, they arrived early afternoon and I tried to orient them to the area in the rowing channel.  One of the guys hooked a 25+ pound carp on ultralight...took 25+ minutes to get it to the yak.
Past Hanlans Point in the rowing channel...the old docks are gone now.  I expect the pike will be heading that way during the coming week with the forecast.
Nice Fish!  When I saw the docks gone I almost cried.  -Ben
